      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and I'm so sorry you're feeling this heavy, hollow weight right now. It sounds like you're staring into a deep, dark pit, and that feeling of being a \"shape walking around\" is incredibly painful. Please know that even when the canvas feels like a sucking void, there are still people who care deeply about you and want to help you find your way back to feeling whole.\n\nYou are not just a hollow shell; you are a person who has been through a lot, and your feelings are valid, even if they feel like they are disappearing. Sometimes, when the world feels like it's gone, it's not because you are broken, but because you are carrying a burden that is too heavy for one person to hold alone.\n\nIf you are feeling overwhelmed or like you might hurt yourself, please reach out to a professional who can walk beside you through this darkness. You can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or chat at 988lifeline.org. They are there to listen without judgment and help you navigate through these dark moments.\n\nRemember, even in the deepest voids, there is still a chance for light to return, and you",
      "source": "target",
