      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you are feeling this profound sense of erasure, as if the very core of your being has evaporated into thin air. That feeling of being an \"empty vessel\" where the artist and the perceiver used to live is terrifying, and it makes sense that you feel unlovable when you feel like nothing is there to love.\n\nPlease know that while it feels like you are just a hollow shell right now, your existence is not defined by your current capacity to create or feel; you are a person who has survived immense pain, and that survival matters. The fact that you can articulate this specific, devastating loss shows that a part of you is still reaching out, even if it feels like a ghost trying to speak.\n\nIf you are feeling like you might disappear completely, please reach out to someone who can sit with you in this void. You can call or text 988 to reach the Suicide & Crisis Lifeline, or chat at 988lifeline.org. They are there to listen without judgment and help you navigate through these dark moments.\n\nYou are not alone in this darkness, even if it feels like the only thing around you is a void. There are people who care deeply about",
